#: 2020-02-14-newsletter-36.md:100
#, no-wrap
msgid "An Adani mine protest with an Australian twist"
msgstr "带有澳大利亚特色的印度阿达尼抗议行动"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-02-14-newsletter-36.md:103
msgid "05 FEB | Munich, Germany"
msgstr "05 二月 | 慕尼黑, 德国"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-02-14-newsletter-36.md:105
msgid "![](/assets/img/blog/2020/02/14/image8.jpg){:.img-fluid}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-02-14-newsletter-36.md:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Rebels stage a “die-in” as Siemens shareholders arrive for the AGM (Photo: Helge Brügner)*\n"
msgstr "*反对者们在西门子股东出席年度股东大会时上演了一场“死亡秀”(图:赫尔格·布鲁格纳)*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-02-14-newsletter-36.md:112
msgid ""
"The [Wangan and Jagalingou First Nation People](https://wanganjagalingou.com."
"au/) are on the [front line in the fight against the Adani Carmichael mine "
"in Australia](https://wanganjagalingou.com.au/we-are-not-just-on-the-"
"frontline-we-are-the-frontline/). With the capacity to export 700,000 "
"million tonnes of carbon dioxide every single year, this **mega-mine would "
"be an environmental disaster.** **Siemens** is the only company left that is "
"willing to provide the signalling systems for the mining operation. "
"**Despite worldwide pressure, Siemens has refused to cancel the contract**.  "
"Australian activists travelled to Germany and were able to **directly "
"address shareholders at the Siemens AGM in Munich** on the 5th February.  "
"Murrawah Johnson, [Varsha Yarman](https://www.kritischeaktionaere.de/en/"
"siemens-2/my-generation-and-future-generations-lives-are-on-the-line-speech-"
"by-varsha-yajman/) and [Dr. Lindsay Simpson](https://www.kritischeaktionaere."
"de/en/siemens-2/siemens-will-be-known-as-accomplice-in-the-death-of-the-"
"great-barrier-reef-speech-by-dr-lindsay-simpson/) spoke about the "
"**Emergency and the impact of the Adani mine**. Fellow rebels onstage "
"translated their speeches into German."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-02-14-newsletter-36.md:114
msgid "![](/assets/img/blog/2020/02/14/image9.jpg){:.img-fluid}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-02-14-newsletter-36.md:116
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Seven rebels locked on with superglue at the Siemens AGM. (Photo: Helge Brügner)*\n"
msgstr "*七名反叛者在西门子年度股东大会上用强力胶把自己黏在门上。(照片:Helge Brugner) *\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-02-14-newsletter-36.md:120
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Rebels showed up in force at the meeting** - some staging a “die-in” at the entrance while seven other rebels locked-on inside the conference hall, and another rebel turned himself into a “[security kangaroo](https://twitter.com/LukasSchnermann/status/1225735510511038465?s=20)” and hopped across the conference floor.\n"
"Annemarie Botzki from XR Deutschland commented : ‘We will fight for our future, Siemens prides itself on taking the lead in the fight against the climate catastrophe and speaks of climate neutrality for 2030, **and in fact the company continues to participate in climate-destroying projects**.’\n"
"Lukas Schnermann added : ‘We therefore demand from Siemens' board members that they implement the contents of their PR methods and **get out of all climate-damaging projects**.’\n"
msgstr ""

